warned by me.\'\n\n8\\. Then the Pratihart _ri_ approached him, saying: \'Sir, you said to me,\n"Pratihart _ri_ , if you, without knowing the deity belonging to the\npratihara, are going to sing it, your head will fall off,"--Which then is that\ndeity?\'\n\n9\\. He said: \'Food (anna). For all these beings\n\np. 21\n\nlive when they partake of food. This is the deity belonging to the pratihara.\nIf, without knowing that deity, you had sung your hymns, your head would have\nfallen off, after you had been warned by me [1](sbe01033.htm#fn_113).\'\n\n* * *\n\n### Footnotes\n\n[19:2](sbe01032.htm#fr_113) Should it be avittva, as in I, 2, 9?\n\n* * *\n\n[Next: I, 12](sbe01033.htm)\n\n'